
@startuml

' Define classes and their attributes and associations

class Home {
}

class Department {
    - name: String
}

class Room {
    - number: int
}

class Bed {
    - bedNumber: int
    + category: Category
}

class Category {
    - typeName: String (e.g., RH, RNH, SF)
    - price: float
}

class Inhabitant {
    - id: int
    - firstName: String
    - lastName: String
    - registrationDate: Date
    + currentStays: List<Stay>
}

class Stay {
    - startDate: Date
    - endDate: Date (optional)
    - status: String (active, suspended, ended)
    + type: Category
    + bed: Bed
    + inhabitant: Inhabitant
}

class Registration {
    - registrationDate: Date
    + inhabitant: Inhabitant
}

class Assessment {
    - needsHelpEating: Boolean
    - needsHelpDressing: Boolean
    - needsHelpPersonalCare: Boolean
    + recommendedCategory: Category
    + inhabitant: Inhabitant
}

class WaitingList {
    + position: int
    + inhabitant: Inhabitant
    + requestedCategory: Category
}

class Proposal {
    - proposalDate: Date
    - responseDeadline: Date
    - accepted: Boolean
    + waitingListEntry: WaitingList
    + bed: Bed
}

class Invoice {
    - issueDate: Date
    - dueDate: Date
    - totalAmount: float
    - outstandingAmount: float
    - status: String (open, paid)
    + stay: Stay
}

class Payment {
    - paymentDate: Date
    - amount: float
    + invoice: Invoice
}

class CreditNote {
    - issueDate: Date
    - amount: float
    + overpaymentInvoice: Invoice
}

class Complaint {
    - description: String
    - resolutionDate: Date
    + invoice: Invoice
}

' Associations and relations

Home "1" --> "many" Department
Department "1" --> "many" Room
Room "1" --> "many" Bed
Bed "1" --> "1" Category
Inhabitant "1" --> "many" Stay
Inhabitant "1" --> "1" Registration
Inhabitant "1" --> "1" Assessment
Assessment "1" --> "1" WaitingList
WaitingList "1" --> "many" Proposal
Proposal "1" --> "1" Bed
Stay "1" --> "1" Bed
Stay "1" --> "1" Category
Stay "1" --> "many" Invoice
Invoice "1" --> "many" Payment
Invoice "0..*" --> "1" CreditNote
Invoice "0..*" --> "1" Complaint

@enduml

---

### Explanation of Key Elements:

- **Home**: Central entity that owns **Departments**.
- **Department → Room → Bed → Category**: Hierarchical structure to manage physical resources.
- **Inhabitant**: Central to all processes. Each has **Registration**, **Assessment**, and multiple **Stays**.
- **WaitingList**: Based on assessment and registration date.
- **Proposal**: Sent when a bed becomes available.
- **Stay**: Can be active, suspended, or ended. Each stay is linked to one **Bed** and one **Category**.
- **Invoice/Payment/CreditNote/Complaint**: Handles billing and financial interactions.
- **Assessment**: Determines which category an inhabitant is eligible for and starts the waiting list process.

